Defendant Kevin R Meltesen in court with attorney Mark E. Kershek.  Kevin M. Osborne appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  The Defendant was sentenced to the following:

IMPOSED AND STAYED SENTENCE OF:   

5 MONTHS JAIL, (consecutive to 14CM2268);

TERM OF PROBATION:  18 MONTHS; (the court would grant early termination of probation based on agents recommendation and completion of all conditions);

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:  
*Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;
*Maintain full time employment and/or combination of schooling 
*No contact with:  Home City Ice, co-defendants, or  Joseph J. and Gregg Z. 
*DNA sample and surcharge waived based on date of violation.
*Any other condition to be determined by agent.
*Perform 75 Hours Community Service. 
*Write letter of apology to all victims. 

RESTITUTION:  $300.00 to Joseph J. and $4,534.00 to Gregg Z. (to be paid as a condition of probation - restitution to be paid before costs or fines);

COURT COSTS:  $253.00 (to be paid as a condition of probation);

The request for EXPUNGEMENT is not granted.
